    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        McCook</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 24, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch No. 4, of 1st of August last, in
                    relation to the visit of Queen Emma to the United States, has been received.</p>
                <p>In reply I have to state that your judicious suggestion in regard to bestowing on
                    her similar attentions to those which she received in England has been
                    anticipated by the President.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward M. McCook,</hi> Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                        >c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
